Welcome to my SecureDrop landing page. Here, you'll find instructions on how to share information and documents with me securely

About this page

I am Espen Andersen, journalist and developer at the Norwegian Broadcast Corporation (NRK). I work with investigative journalism and storytelling for NRK's online edition nrk.no. This page is part of my private web site.

You probably landed here through my regular pages at espenandersen.no, or you may have received one of my printed contact cards.

This is for getting in touch with me personally. You should use NRKs own SecureDrop portal for anonymous inquiries to the news room in general. Go to nrkbeta.no/tips for instructions on how to use NRK's SecureDrop implementation.

How to contact me

Since you are already using Tor, it's simple:

  1. If you're not already in one, find an internet caf√© other than your regular hangout. Use the network there.
  2. From TorBrowser, navigate to lijbt6ju7m6opkzb.onion and follow the instructions there. Click «Submit Documents» to start the submission process.
  3. You will be given a nick name, which is very important to remember in order to receive feedback on your submission. This is the only means for me to send you a reply.

SecureDrop portal's front page.

Verify this page

This page is cryptographically signed by me. You should verify that the signature coincides with my public encryption key, having the following fingerprint:

BA7E AC9F 78DA C483 B0C7 DE79 DD32 F64A 341F 8E25

The public key can be obtained from my website at espenandersen.no/pgp.pub.asc or from sks-keyservers.net.

You can verify this page by saving the page source to an .asc file and verify it in PGP. Alternatively, you can save it as a .html file and run the following command on Linux or OS X:

gpg --verify [html_source_file]

where [html_source_file] is the path to the .html file with this page's source code.
